text.tspan: Age-standardized death rate from non-communicable diseases, United
The age-standardized death rate measures the number of deaths per 100,000 individuals, corrected for age differences by
normalising to a constant, reference population distribution. The age-standardization death rate therefore corrects for both
changes/differences in population sizes, and the influence of a young or aging population.
Source: Institute for Health Metrics and Evaluation (IHME)
